BEFORE(num split string)
BEFORE(split string)
  Returns the portion of string that comes before the num-th instance
  of split.

  If num is omitted, the first instance of split is used.

Examples:
  before(hi this)		- Returns "t"
  before(1 ! one!two!three)	- Returns "one"
  before(2 ! one!two!three)	- Returns "one!two"
  before(-1 ! four!five!six)	- Returns "four!five"

See also:
  FUNCTIONS AFTER
